	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary76.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date when="1862-06-11">Wednesday 11th</date></dateline>
				<p>This was a <name type="weather">pleasant</name> day. I went to town with
						<persName key="Aaron Smith"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper006"
						>Smith</persName>
					<persName key="H. Co'y McCormick"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper153"
						>McCormick</persName> &amp; <persName key="Peter Koser"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper067"
						>Cozer</persName>. I met <persName key="Thomas Grier"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper076"
						>Tom Grier</persName> &amp; read a read a <objectName type="readible"
						>paper</objectName> of the 6th. There was nothing doing at all. Dined as
						<orgName type="military">the Union</orgName> &amp; got back to <placeName
						type="camp">camp</placeName> for <objectName type="clothing"
						>dress</objectName> parade. I saw <persName key="Dr. Cutter"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper124"
						>Dr Cutter</persName> and told him how our men were used in regard to
						<objectName type="equipment">rations</objectName> at <placeName type="city"
						cert="high" key="Beaufort"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl005"
							>Beaufort</placeName>. He
					intimated he had no control &amp; that the party that were in there were at
					fault. I believe I will raise a row to <persName key="Gen. Jesse Reno"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper086"
						>Gen. Reno</persName>. </p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
